# Resources Directory

## Required Ishihara Plate Images

Place the following images in this directory:
- **ishihara_1.jpg** - Control plate (both normal and color blind see "12")
- **ishihara_3.jpg** - Normal sees "6", red/green deficiency sees "5"
- **ishihara_11.jpg** - Normal sees "6", red/green deficiency sees nothing
- **ishihara_19.jpg** - Normal sees nothing, red/green deficiency sees "2"

## Where to Get the Images

### Option 1: Wikipedia
Download Ishihara test plates from:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ishihara_test

### Option 2: Public Domain Sources
Search for "Ishihara test plates public domain" or use research-approved sources.

### Option 3: Create Your Own
For testing only, you can create simple dot patterns that simulate the test.

## Image Requirements

- **Format:** JPG (JPEG)
- **Size:** At least 800x800 pixels recommended
- **Quality:** High resolution for accurate testing
- **Shape:** Square images work best (will be displayed as circles)

